# Project Context

## PROJECT OVERVIEW
This file contains project-specific guidelines and patterns for the Cursor Rules Framework.

## PROJECT-SPECIFIC PATTERNS
- **Framework Integration**: Django, Oracle DB, React, Terraform, Ruby, RDS, EC2
- **Session Management**: Process status tracking, state transitions, error handling
- **Compliance Requirements**: HIPAA compliance, PII protection, audit trails

## PROJECT CONTEXT
- **Technology Stack**: Django backend with Oracle database
- **Frontend**: Javascript components with modern UI patterns
- **Data Management**: Oracle database with specific schema requirements
- **Deployment**: Isolated EC2 instances (dev, stage, prod) using GitHub Actions and SSH deploy keys. All deployments are push-triggered and environment-scoped.
- **Stack**: Each instance runs Ubuntu 24.04 with Gunicorn and NGINX, using systemd for process management. Static assets served by NGINX.
- **Secrets & Transit Encryption**: Secrets and environment-specific config are pulled from AWS Secrets Manager. HTTPS enforced using SSL.
- **Development**: Localhost and https://comp-dev.mwahq.com on Dev Oracle db
- **Stage**: https://comp-stage.mwahq.com on Stage Oracle db
- **Production**: Not yet deployed.

